Manages user registration by sending a POST request to a specified endpoint (/api/v1/employee/register) with the user's registration details.
Uses Axios for making HTTP requests.
Utilizes React hooks such as useState, useContext, and useEffect for managing state and side effects.
Redirects the user to the /loggedIn route if they are already authenticated (i.e., if auth.token exists).
Provides an option to toggle password visibility.
Handles form submission and loading state while waiting for the server response.

The appearance is defined by the JSX returned by the component.
It consists of a <section> element with the id form, which likely encapsulates the entire sign-up form.
The form includes input fields for full name, email, branch, password, and confirm password, along with a button for submitting the form.
There's a link/button for users who already have an account to navigate to the login page.

Overall, the Signup component provides a user-friendly interface for users to register with the application, handles registration requests, and provides feedback to the user based on the server response.